def solve(n):
    SUMA = 2050
    if n % SUMA == 0:
        n //= SUMA
        ans = 0
        while n > 0:
            m = n % 10
            ans += m
            n //= 10
        return ans
    return -1

    t = int(input())
    for i in range(t):
        n = int(input())
        ans = solve(n)
        print(ans)

import sys

def solve(a):
    if a % 2050:
        return -1
    res = 0
    x = a // 2050
    for c in str(x):
        res += int(c)
    return res
n = int(sys.stdin.readline())
for _ in range(n):
    a = int(sys.stdin.readline())
    res = solve(a)
    print(res)
